issue.title: eKnights list
issue.body: Instead of adding eKnights manually, why not scanning and creating a dynamic list, based on: https://api.github.com/orgs/hasadna/repos ?

comment.body:
Because we don't want to...
We talked about it on Monday...

On the list(this one https://api.github.com/orgs/hasadna/repos) there is a lot of repos which are:

1. Not an eKnight (https://github.com/hasadna/django-activity-stream for example)
2. Part of eKnight but have there own repo:

 Take https://github.com/hasadna/ok-static  for example:
  its part of open knesset eKnight but its not in the open knesset repo.
  If we don't map each repo manually we don't have any way to know both of the repos belongs to the same eKnight.
